 "awd_abstract_narration": "AST-0504947\r\nBurrows, Adam\r\nUniversity of Arizona\r\nMulti-Dimensional Simulations of Core-Collapse Supernovae\r\nABSTRACT\r\nRecently developed fully 2D multi-group, multi-angle radiation/hydrodynamics codes\r\nwill be used to investigate the roles of progenitor rotation, aspherical neutrino emissions,\r\nhydrodynamic instabilities, and initial mass on neutrino driven mechanisms of core\r\ncollapse supernovae. The need for this work is motivated by the significant uncertainties\r\nin the process by which such supernovae explode (e.g., how is the stalled shock\r\nrevived?). Special attention will be paid to the role of rotation and anisotropic neutrino\r\nheating on the viability of the supernova explosion. Beyond this, several other aspects\r\nwill also be explored including: resulting iron distributions, the degree of top-bottom\r\nasymmetry, different treatments/coding of the underlying physics, neutrino and\r\ngravitational wave signatures, and pulsar kick mechanisms. The work here will directly\r\ncontribute to the training of two graduate students, as well as improve our understanding\r\nof these important and complex events.",
